      "side": 1,
      "message": "[error] Line 29: 🔴 Detaching the current worker avoids `std::thread::join()` throwing, but it does not make self-destruction safe: after `join()` returns, the detached worker can continue unwinding back into the pool worker loop and access `running_`, `tasks_`, `mutex_`, or `cv_` after `threads_.clear()` and object destruction. The fix should ensure `ThreadPool` is never destroyed/joined from one of its own workers, or make the worker exit path avoid touching destroyed pool state before allowing destruction to complete.",
